description:
&lt;p&gt;We are seeking a dedicated and proactive clinical pharmacist to work as part of the Community Services Pharmacy Team. Based in Exmouth Community Hospital, this position will support service provision to the inpatient bedded unit as well as a medicines optimisation service to housebound patients in their own homes. Our pharmacy services are highly respected and we work closely with clinical and social care staff in the hospital and community. Our primary focus is to achieve the best quality of patient care, so the desire to improve patient outcomes and the willingness to learn and develop is essential.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Exmouth hospital is an intermediate care unit with inpatient facilities for those requiring medical care or therapy who do not require acute care in a general hospital. This varied and interesting role will involve daily patient contact to maintain a high quality of prescribing and clinical care for patients. You will work alongside all multidisciplinary team members to optimise prescribing decisions for patients. You will help find solutions to all manner of medicine related problems and have the opportunity to shape the pharmacy service you deliver. You will work closely across the primary / secondary care interface to improve the quality of patient care and experience.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Referrals for our ‘at home’ service are for patients with complex medication needs who require medicines management interventions to maintain independence in their own homes. This rewarding role involves making contact with patients by phone, video calling or face to face. Our team members liaise with GPs to make personalised medication recommendations and suggest practical implementations to assist medicines adherence.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Candidates should have excellent verbal and written communication skills and the ability to work as part of a team. You will be organised and able to adapt to the changing needs of patients with an ability to prioritise workload at short notice in response to the demands of the service.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will be expected to provide supervision, training and support to junior staff; cover other clinical localities when required and facilitate medicines related training to members of the multidisciplinary team.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;In return, the provision of support and training to progress you and your professional development is highly important to us. The Trust has recently launched an electronic prescribing and patient record system across acute and community services, which is transforming the way we care for patients. This is an evolving process and gives us all the opportunity to influence the future of pharmacy services.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will work alongside a small pharmacy team based in Exmouth and be an active member of the wider community and acute pharmacy team, which offers continued peer support.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If you would like to be part of this friendly team, we would like to hear from you. Applications are invited from clinical pharmacists with appropriate skills and knowledge from any sector. You must be a registered pharmacist with the General Pharmaceutical Council and have an ability to travel to various locations. Further details can be found in the job description.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Hours: Full time (Applications for part time will be considered)&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Salary: Band 7 £38,890 to £44,503 per annum pro rata&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Location: Exmouth Hospital&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further information or an informal discussion please contact&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Community Clinical Pharmacy Manager: 07825 904604 / suzanne.bidwell@nhs.net&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Integrated Pharmacy Services Lead: 01392 402427 /samsmith2@nhs.net&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Please note that you will be notified via email regarding the result of your application. Interview date is &lt;strong&gt;Thursday 3rd December 2020&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Due to the anticipated high number of applications for this post we reserve the right to close the vacancy before the closure date.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Our vision is to provide safe, high quality seamless services delivered with courtesy and respect. To achieve our vision we expect all our staff to uphold our Trust values. Our Trust values are: &lt;br /&gt; Honesty, Openness &amp; Integrity&lt;br /&gt; Fairness&lt;br /&gt; Inclusion &amp; Collaboration&lt;br /&gt; Respect &amp; Dignity&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;***Preference will be given to staff with ‘Priority’ and &#39;At Risk&#39; status including NHS At Risk staff throughout Devon.***&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;DUE TO THE ANTICIPATED HIGH NUMBER OF APPLICATIONS FOR THIS POST WE RESERVE THE RIGHT TO CLOSE THE VACANCY BEFORE THE CLOSING DATE.&lt;/p&gt;
